INSERT INTO `wp_6_posts` VALUES (212,2,'2014-10-27 17:54:19','2014-10-27 17:54:19','[vimeo id=\"109945858\" align=\"center\" mode=\"normal\" autoplay=\"no\" loop=\"yes\" aspect_ratio=\"16:9\" maxwidth=\"760\"]<!--more-->\r\n\r\nAfter 3 consecutively sold out product management conferences in London, we\'ve learned a thing or two about what makes a great conference.\r\n\r\nMind the Product started in 2012 with 600 passionate product managers, designers and developers joining us at the Mermaid Theater in London for a day of inspiration, connection and partying.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>The talks were the best talks I\'ve heard in a very long time. This was big. </blockquote>\r\n<em>- Marty Cagan</em>\r\n\r\nWe came back with even more great speakers for a repeat in 2013 and - realizing we’d outgrown our space - in 2014 we moved to a huge new venue, pulling together over 1,000 passionate product people from 39 countries. The first 150 early bird tickets sold out in under 60 seconds.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>It was really obvious from the beginning that being together helped, not only move our own careers forward, but move the discipline of product management forward. </blockquote>\r\n<em>- Aziz Musa, Director of Products, Eva</em>\r\n\r\nNow we’re excited to bring our conference to San Francisco. We’ll be coming with the same mix of amazing content – both inspirational and practical – socializing - over good food and coffee - and discussion on products and innovation that runs late into the night over far too many drinks.\r\n\r\n\r\n<blockquote>It\'s always nice when you\'re working on digital stuff in your own company, in your own bubble, that you get to step out of that seat for a while and reflect on what it is that you do every day, but also be around people that are also thinking about the work we do. I wish there was something like this in the US. </blockquote>\r\n<em>- Charles Adler, Co-Founder and Creative Director, Kickstarter</em>','A history of amazing product management conferences','','publish','open','open','','history-amazing-product-management-conferences','','','2015-01-12 11:16:11','2015-01-12 11:16:11','',0,'http://mtpcon.com/sf/?p=212',0,'post','',0);
