INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (211,2,'2014-10-30 00:50:42','2014-10-30 00:50:42','The Mind the Product conferences are brought to you by a team of product managers who spend all day building start-ups, and all night building a community for their product manager peers.<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://twitter.com/bfgmartin\" title=\"Martin Eriksson on Twitter\">Martin</a> is the founder of <a href=\"http://www.producttank.com\" title=\"Product Management Meetups\">ProductTank</a>, a monthly product management meet up in London, which has been running for four years and now has over 3,000 members and draws in 300+ attendees to every meetup. It has also gone international, with meetups in 25 cities around the world.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://twitter.com/simplybastow\" title=\"Janna Bastow on Twitter\">Janna</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/simoncast\" title=\"Simon Cast on Twitter\">Simon</a> are the co-founders and organizers of <a href=\"http://www.productcamplondon.com\" title=\"ProductCamp London\">ProductCamp London</a> – a collaborative, user organized unconference based on the global ProductCamp.org.\r\n\r\nTogether we joined forces to found <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com\" title=\"Mind the Product\">Mind the Product</a> - a blog and conference focused on building a community for product management, which we describe as the intersection between design, technology and business.  \r\n\r\nWe are funded by our generous sponsors and ticket sales, and driven by a passion for great products and the people who build them.','By product people, for product people','','publish','open','open','','by-product-people-for-product-people','','','2014-10-30 16:11:46','2014-10-30 16:11:46','',0,'http://mtpcon.com/?p=211',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (212,2,'2014-10-30 00:54:08','2014-10-30 00:54:08','Mind the Product has featured diverse speakers from all over the world, all of whom are experienced, hands-on practitioners of the art of product management. Every year we’re joined by new product superheros who are keen to share their experiences and hard won lessons with our audience.<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<blockquote>The talks were the best talks I’ve heard in a very long time. This was big.\r\n<cite>Marty Cagan</cite></blockquote>\r\n\r\n<h1>2014</h1>\r\nKathy Sierra - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/09/kathy-sierra-building-badass-users/\" title=\"Kathy Sierra - Building badass users\">Build badass users</a>\r\nDave Wascha - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/10/dave-wascha-inside-mind-product-manager/\" title=\"Dave Wascha - Inside the mind of the product manager\">Inside the mind of the product manager</a>\r\nNir Eyal - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/10/nir-eyal-building-habit-forming-products/\" title=\"Nir Eyal – Building habit-forming products\">Building habit-forming products</a>\r\nDes Traynor - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/10/des-traynor-product-strategy-growing-company/\" title=\"Des Traynor – Product strategy in a growing company\">Product strategy in a growing company</a>\r\nIrene Au - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/10/irene-au-design-is-as-important-as-technology/\" title=\"Irene Au – Design is as important as technology\">Design is as important as technology</a>\r\nFred Destin - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/10/fred-destin-you-need-to-embrace-chaos-to-succeed/\" title=\"Fred Destin – You need to embrace chaos to succeed\">You need to embrace chaos to succeed</a>\r\nLeisa Reichelt - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/11/leisa-reichelt-changing-organisations-to-improve-products/\" title=\"Leisa Reichelt – Changing organisations to improve products\">Changing organisations to improve products</a>\r\nAlex Osterwalder - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/11/alex-osterwalder-designing-your-value-proposition/\" title=\"Alex Osterwalder – Designing your Value Proposition\">Designing your Value Proposition</a>\r\nGenevieve Bell - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2015/01/human-digital-world-lessons-intersection-tech-culture/\" title=\"Genevieve Bell - Being Human in a Digital World: Lessons from the intersection of tech & culture\">Being Human in a Digital World: Lessons from the intersection of tech & culture</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h1>2013</h1>\r\nPaul Adams - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/11/video-next-product-canvas/\" title=\"The Next Product Canvas\">The next product canvas</a>\r\nCennydd Bowles - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/02/video-product-design-tomorrow/\" title=\"Product Design for Tomorrow\">Product Design for Tomorrow</a>\r\nGeorge Berkowski - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/12/video-how-to-build-a-billion-dollar-app/\" title=\"How to Build a Billion Dollar App\">How to Build a Billion Dollar App</a>\r\nAndy Budd - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/02/video-design-competitive-advantage/\" title=\"Design as Competitive Advantage\">Design as Competitive Advantage</a>\r\nBrant Cooper & Patrick Vlaskovits - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/01/video-lean-product-development/\" title=\"Lean Product Development\">Lean Product Development</a>\r\nKelly Goto - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/12/video-beyond-usable-mapping-emotion-experience/\" title=\"Beyond Usable - Mapping Emotion to Experience\">Beyond usable – mapping emotion to experience</a>\r\nTim Harford - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/01/innovations-that-matter/\" title=\"Innovations that Matter\">Innovations that Matter</a>\r\nAziz Musa - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/12/video-delivering-a-pure-product/\" title=\"Delivering a Pure Product\">Delivering a Pure Product</a>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<h1>2012</h1>\r\nCharles Adler - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/01/the-antithesis-of-a-product-process/\" title=\"The antithesis of product process\">The antithesis of product process</a>\r\nMarty Cagan - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2012/12/video-marty-cagans-top-10-tips-to-making-products-customers-love/\" title=\"Top 10 tips to making products people love\">Top 10 tips to making products people love</a>\r\nTom Coates - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/02/does-my-fridge-need-twitter/\" title=\"Does my fridge need twitter?\">Does my fridge need twitter?</a>\r\nTom Chi - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2012/12/rapid-prototyping-google-glass-by-tom-chi/\" title=\"Rapid prototyping Google Glass\">Rapid prototyping Google Glass</a>\r\nHannah Donovan & Matthew Ogle - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/01/evoking-real-world-experiences-with-a-product-macguffin/\" title=\"Evoking real world experiences with a product macguffin\">Evoking real-world experiences</a>\r\nJohn Earner - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/03/what-games-can-teach-us-about-product-development/\" title=\"What games can teach us about product development\">What games can teach us about product development</a>\r\nTom Hulme - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/01/video-is-purpose-the-new-pivot/\" title=\"Is purpose the new pivot?\">Is purpose the new pivot?</a>\r\nTom Loosemore - <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2013/02/video-proper-product-management-in-large-organisations-do-it-with-jazz/\" title=\"Product management in large organisations\">Product management in large organisations, do it with Jazz</a>','3 Years of amazing product conferences','','publish','open','open','','3-years-of-amazing-product-conferences','','','2015-01-06 18:49:52','2015-01-06 18:49:52','',0,'http://mtpcon.com/?p=212',0,'post','',0);
INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES (213,2,'2014-10-30 00:54:56','2014-10-30 00:54:56','On September 12, 2014, over 1,000 passionate product people from 39 countries around the world gathered in London for our third annual conference, making it the largest gathering of product managers ever!<!--more-->\r\n\r\n[vimeo id=\"106530931\" align=\"center\" mode=\"normal\" autoplay=\"no\" aspect_ratio=\"16:9\" maxwidth=\"720px\"]\r\n\r\nAs usual we had an amazing mix of speakers, covering both practical tips and experiences as well as inspirational thought leadership on the future of product management, development and design.\r\n\r\nJust as importantly, the room was packed with passionate product managers, designers, engineers and founders who used every opportunity – from the lunch buffet to the free-flowing drinks at the after party – to share war stories and connect with a larger product community.\r\n\r\n<blockquote>I’m a product manager and you are my tribe. This tribe keeps growing and it’s amazing to see. Next year we’ll probably have to move to the Wembley stadium.\r\n<cite>Dave Wascha, Chief Product Officer Moo.com.</site></blockquote>\r\n\r\nTo read our full report from the conference, check out <a href=\"http://www.mindtheproduct.com/2014/09/mtpcon-2014-were-doing-the-right-thing/\" title=\"MTPcon 2014: We’re doing the right thing\">MTPcon 2014: We’re doing the right thing</a>.','Mind the Product London 2014 in review','','publish','open','open','','mind-the-product-london-2014-in-review','','','2014-10-30 16:38:23','2014-10-30 16:38:23','',0,'http://mtpcon.com/?p=213',0,'post','',0);
